gnus</i> ‘fist’)."],"variants":[{"name":"Poynor","meanings":["English (Staffordshire and Leicestershire; of Norman origin): variant of   Poyner  ."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir Thomas Poyner was born in 1463, in Longnor, Shropshire, England, his father, John Poyner of Bedeslow, was 20 and his mother, Jane Lee De Langley, was 26. He married Lucia Eaton about 1484, in Shropshire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He died in 1538, in his hometown, at the age of 75, and was buried in Shropshire, England."},"et":{"1463–1538":"1463–1538","1467–1485":"1467–1485","1485–1543":"1485–1543","1485–1564":"1485–1564","1443–1462":"1443–1462","1437–1500":"1437–1500","1437":"1437","1500":"1500","1467":"1467","1543":"1543","1443":"1443","1564":"1564","1463":"1463","1485":"1485","1462":"1462","Abt. 1485":"umbes 1485","about 1484":"umbes 1484","1538":"1538","Bestowe, Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Shropshire, England":"Shropshire, England","Beslow, Shropshire, England.":"Shropshire, England","Longnor, Shropshire, England":"Longnor, Shropshire, England","Langley, Shropshire, England, United Kingdom":"Langley by Milson, Shropshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1463–1538":"1463–1538","1467–1485":"1467–1485","1485–1543":"1485–1543","1485–1564":"1485–1564","1443–1462":"1443–1462","1437–1500":"1437–1500","1437":"1437","1500":"1500","1467":"1467","1543":"1543","1443":"1443","1564":"1564","1463":"1463","1